==English==

===Etymology===
From Old Norse ''[[skyrta]]'', from Germanic ''*skurtijon''.  Compare ''[[shirt]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-skirt.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)t|-ɜː(r)t]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#An article of [[clothing]], usually worn by [[woman|women]] and [[girl]]s, that hangs from the [[waist]] and covers the lower part of the body.
#The part of a [[dress]] or [[robe]] that hangs below the [[waist]].
#Something resembling a skirt.
#{{slang}} A woman.
#A part that serves as a [[border]] or [[edging]].

